posts.raw_content:
Long story short, I was on the fast track to death. Addicted to vodka - drinking every single day, morning afternoon and night. At a certain point it is not the excess of alcohol that will kill you, but rather the withdrawals, so I had to keep drinking from feeling sick. 

However, last week I truly believe it was God himself that told me to go detox and to finally get rid of this DEMON that was plaguing me. Ever wonder why alcohol is called “spirits?” I know this is a lifelong battle, and not drinking is just one part of the battle. But at least I physically got it out of my system. For example, finally no more shakes! (Well, at least decreased by about 90% so far). 

I’ve had bad experiences with hospitals before, but now that I’ve reflected on it, God made this experience perfect for me. The entire staff was great, I had zero sense of malicious intent from anyone there, the withdrawals sucked but the meds and praying definitely helped. EVERYTHING that I thought bad was going to happen or could or might happen *did not happen*. 

I honestly believed I could never stop alcohol. As the AA Big Book calls it - cunning, baffling, powerful.  But only through God’s strength and fearlessness was I able to stop. 

Alcohol is the devil. Quit while you can, as it does nobody ANY good and only serves to weaken and destroy you mentally, physically and emotionally. 

Stay sober as we will need to be on high alert these upcoming times with all the communist bastards attacking and overthrowing our nation. God bless you all ❤️
